# Difference Between Half Adder and Full Adder

- The main difference between a [[61-Archive/20220318121832-half-adder|Half Adder]] and a [[61-Archive/20220318121918-full-adder|Full Adder]] is that the [[61-Archive/20220318121918-full-adder|Full Adder]] has three inputs.
- The [[61-Archive/20220318121918-full-adder|Full Adder]] accepts two 1-bit binary numbers and one input carry to generate a sum output and an output carry.
